FBIS3-38151 "drweu020_o_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-020 Document Type:Daily Report 31 Jan 1994 CYPRUS Indirect Talks Reportedly To Begin in Nicosia `Soon' TA2901181094 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1630 GMT 29 Jan 94 TA2901181094 Nicosia Bayrak Radio Language: Turkish Article Type:BFN [Text] The indirect talks on the confidence-building measures drawn up by UN Secretary General Butrus-Ghali to help solve the Cyprus problem will soon begin in Lefkosa [Nicosia]. Based on diplomatic sources in Lefkosa, ANATOLIA reported that with the second letter he sent to the UN secretary general, President Rauf Denktas narrowed Greek Cypriot leader Glavkos Kliridhis' area of maneuvering. ANATOLIA reports that unless Kliridhis creates a new conflict issue, there is no reason why the indirect talks should not begin soon.
